					<head>Karaite commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>Fragments of Arabic translation and commentaries on the book of Exodus.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="87v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Exodus</title>
							<note>Contains Exodus 13:17-15:1, 15:22-17:7, 18:1-21:36, 22:4-30:21, 30:33-32:29, 33:12-34:26. Pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, with a translation and short commentary in (Judeo-)Arabic.<p>The Hebrew text is arranged into the following sections (corresponding to parashiyot petuhot u-setumot): chapters 13:17-22; 14:1-14; 14:15-25, 26-31; 15:1; 15:22-26; 15:27-16:3; 16:4-10; 16:11-27, 28-36; 17:1-4, 5-7; 18:1-12, 13-27; 19:1-25; 20:1, 2-6, 7, 8-11, 12, 13-17, 18-21, 22-26; 21:1-6, 7-11, 12-13, 14, 15-17, 18-19, 20-21, 22-25, 26-27, 28-32, 33-34, 35-36; 22:4, 5, 6-8, 9-12, 13-14, 15-16, 17, 18, 19-23, 24-26, 27-30; 23:1-3, 4, 5, 6-9, 10-19, 20-25, 26-33; 24:1-11, 12-18; 25:1-9, 10-16, 17-22, 23-30, 31-40; 26:1-6, 7-14, 15-30 (verse 22 added in the margin); 31-37; 27:1-8, 9-19, 21-21; 28:1-5, 6-12, 13-14, 15-17, 18-29, 30, 31-35, 36-43; 29:11-37, 38-46; 30:1-10, 11-16, 17-21, 33b, 34-38; 31:1-11, 12-17; 31:18-32:6; 32:7-14, 15-29; 33:12-16, 17-23; 34:1-10, 11-26.</p>
								<p>Each of the above sections is followed by the corresponding portion of the translation and commentary, both of which are distinguished from the text by smaller writing.</p>
								<p>The end of a section is marked by a standard blessing formula.</p>
								<p>The number of verses in each weekly parashah is registered at the end.</p>
								<p>Some scant masoretic notes, including the marking of 'ketiv', are included.</p>
								<p>Quotes several Karaite grammarians and other authorities, e.g. ʻAli ibn Sulaiman, Abu lʻFaraj Furkan, Abu ʻAli, David ben Boʻaz.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>The translation is often in agreement with the corresponding portions in Or. 2545 by <persName role="author">Abu al-Faraj Furḳan ibn ʾAsad</persName>.</filiation>
							<decoNote type="other">
								<locus n="1v, 16v, 28v, 45r, 57v, 71r"/>Numerous decorated panels inserted into the body of the text, in colours and gold, at the end of each weekly parashah.</decoNote>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
